## 6. Source Code & Implementation Details
*(Note for the student: Print these essential snippets to show your examiner exactly where the core HTML and CSS are used).*

**Project Architecture Structure:**
* `index.html` - The primary HTML entry point for the entire application.
* `src/index.css` - Custom CSS rules and global theme variables.
* `src/pages/` - UI layouts written in JSX (HTML within JavaScript).
* `src/components/` - Reusable UI HTML structures (Navbar, Buttons).

### A. The Core HTML Foundation (`index.html`)
Even though the project uses a modern framework, it runs entirely out of a single standard HTML file where scripts are injected.
```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Pulse of the Community</title>
    <meta name="description" content="Pulse of the Community project">
  </head>
  <body>
    <!-- The main HTML container where our dynamic application renders -->
    <div id="root"></div>
    <script type="module" src="/src/main.tsx"></script>
  </body>
</html>
```

